Package org.melior.service.mongo

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    MongoCollection<T>
    A MongoDB collection which is registered with a MongoListener for processing.
    MongoListener<T>
    Implements an easy to use, auto-configuring MongoDB listener which listens to registered MongoDB collections and processes any new managed items which are added to the collections.
    MongoListenerBuilder<T>
    Convenience class for building a MongoListener.
    MongoListenerConfig
    Configuration parameters for a MongoListener, with defaults.
    MongoRequestInterceptor<T>
    Intercepts any managed items that have been added to a MongoDB collection after they have been retrieved by the MongoListener but before they haven been processed, and routes them past the configured WorkManager to allow the WorkManager to control the flow of the items through the application.
    MongoService
    A base class for service implementations that process managed items from MongoDB collections.
    MongoSession

    Enum Description
    ListenerState
    The state of the MongoListener which listens to a MongoDB collection.
